WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.549 --> 00:00:04.407
I think if the wedding invitations
were left up to men...

2
00:00:04.408 --> 00:00:08.723
we'd just drive around sticking
fliers in windshields. You know.

3
00:00:10.090 --> 00:00:11.388
Not even typed up either.

4
00:00:11.466 --> 00:00:14.188
Just magic markers.
xeroxed. you know;

5
00:00:14.261 --> 00:00:16.152
"Party."

6
00:00:18.432 --> 00:00:20.821
What's needed
is a divorce announcement.

7
00:00:20.893 --> 00:00:23.828
"Mr. and Mrs. Fred Johnson
request the honour of your presence...

8
00:00:23.896 --> 00:00:29.785
at the returning of their daughter
back to Mr. and Mrs. Fred Johnson."

9
00:00:36.325 --> 00:00:38.252
- Hi.
- Hi. can I help you?

10
00:00:38.327 --> 00:00:42.093
- Yes. we'd like wedding invitations.
- Oh. well. congratulations.

11
00:00:42.165 --> 00:00:43.593
- Thank you.
- Yeah. thank you.

12
00:00:43.666 --> 00:00:45.011
- When's the wedding?
- June.

13
00:00:45.084 --> 00:00:50.012
- Late June.
- We have quite a few to pick from.

14
00:00:50.089 --> 00:00:53.689
They're arranged in order of price.
The most expensive are in the front.

15
00:01:00.016 --> 00:01:01.776
I don't know. what about this one?

16
00:01:02.644 --> 00:01:06.445
To tell you the truth. they haven't
made those for a number of years.

17
00:01:06.523 --> 00:01:09.079
I might have some boxes
in our warehouse in New Jersey.

18
00:01:09.151 --> 00:01:12.002
- I'd have to check.
- Oh. no. George. that's so ugly.

19
00:01:12.070 --> 00:01:13.581
We don't want that.

20
00:01:13.655 --> 00:01:16.959
What's the difference?
You just read it and mail it right back.

21
00:01:17.034 --> 00:01:19.422
- These ones.
- Why don't they make them anymore?

22
00:01:19.495 --> 00:01:23.544
Well. for one thing.
the glue isn't very adhesive.

23
00:01:23.624 --> 00:01:25.966
It takes a lot of moisture
to make them stick.

24
00:01:26.168 --> 00:01:28.640
So we pick up some Elmer's.

25
00:01:31.590 --> 00:01:33.268
All right.

26
00:01:33.384 --> 00:01:35.441
Do you see what I do for you?

27
00:01:37.304 --> 00:01:39.112
- Hey. Kramer.
- Hey. George.

28
00:01:39.765 --> 00:01:42.487
- Lilly.
- No. Susan.

29
00:01:42.560 --> 00:01:45.827
- No. no. it's Lilly.
- I think I know my own name.

30
00:01:45.897 --> 00:01:47.277
It's Susan.

31
00:01:48.024 --> 00:01:51.291
Well. you look like a Lilly.

32
00:01:55.240 --> 00:01:56.917
It's coming. Jerry. it's coming.

33
00:01:56.991 --> 00:01:59.843
- What's coming?
- The day.

34
00:01:59.911 --> 00:02:01.920
The day.

35
00:02:01.996 --> 00:02:04.848
We ordered
the wedding invitations today.

36
00:02:04.916 --> 00:02:07.768
Nothing can stop it now. nothing.

37
00:02:08.128 --> 00:02:10.683
It's here. It's happening.

38
00:02:10.755 --> 00:02:14.225
Can I do this? I can't do this.
Look at me. Look at me. I can't do this.

39
00:02:14.301 --> 00:02:16.440
I can't do it.
Help me. Jerry. help me.

40
00:02:16.511 --> 00:02:19.149
Just break it off with her.
Tell her it's over.

41
00:02:19.765 --> 00:02:21.193
I can't.

42
00:02:21.266 --> 00:02:23.193
- Why not?
- Because I can't face that scene.

43
00:02:23.268 --> 00:02:25.361
You know what kind of a scene
that would be?

44
00:02:25.437 --> 00:02:28.622
I'd rather be unhappy for the rest
of my life than to go through that.

45
00:02:28.691 --> 00:02:32.705
I can't. I've tried to psych myself up
a million times. I can't go through that.

46
00:02:32.778 --> 00:02:34.871
All right. take it easy.
Just take it easy.

47
00:02:37.032 --> 00:02:39.505
- What about a letter?
- A letter?

48
00:02:39.577 --> 00:02:41.716
I write a letter
and then I go to China.

49
00:02:43.122 --> 00:02:46.887
I disappear in a sea of people
for. like. six months. a year.

50
00:02:46.959 --> 00:02:49.847
You know.
just while things simmer down.

51
00:02:50.254 --> 00:02:53.558
"Dear Susan. I'm sorry.

52
00:02:53.716 --> 00:02:55.809
I made a terrible mistake.

53
00:02:55.885 --> 00:02:59.401
I'm really. really sorry."

54
00:03:00.306 --> 00:03:03.407
- That's it?
- What. too short?

55
00:03:03.476 --> 00:03:05.783
- Seems a little short. yeah.
- A little short.

56
00:03:05.979 --> 00:03:08.237
You can't go to China.
What about your job?

57
00:03:08.315 --> 00:03:10.870
Right. My job.

58
00:03:10.942 --> 00:03:13.450
So write a letter
and move to Staten lsland.

59
00:03:13.528 --> 00:03:16.748
It's easier to blend into a sea of people
in Staten lsland than China.

60
00:03:17.532 --> 00:03:20.420
Yeah. yeah. Staten lsland.

61
00:03:20.744 --> 00:03:24.260
- How do I get the rest of my clothes?
- You come back for your clothes.

62
00:03:24.331 --> 00:03:27.432
- I'm not going back in there.
- So forget about your clothes.

63
00:03:27.835 --> 00:03:31.351
Well. I'm not starting up
a whole new wardrobe now!

64
00:03:32.464 --> 00:03:35.850
Freedom and no clothes is a lot better
than no freedom with clothes.

65
00:03:36.260 --> 00:03:38.436
If she would just
take a plane somewhere.

66
00:03:38.512 --> 00:03:39.941
And what. hope for a crash?

67
00:03:41.015 --> 00:03:42.277
It happens.

68
00:03:42.349 --> 00:03:44.905
Do you know the odds on a crash?
It's a million to one.

69
00:03:45.353 --> 00:03:49.367
It's something. It's hope.

70
00:03:50.691 --> 00:03:52.167
- Hey. Hey!
- Hey.

71
00:03:52.235 --> 00:03:54.292
Georgie. you know
what I just realized?

72
00:03:54.529 --> 00:03:57.879
The wedding is like a month away.

73
00:03:58.366 --> 00:03:59.960
- Elaine.
- What?

74
00:04:00.034 --> 00:04:03.219
Oh. by the way. what am I gonna
get to be in the wedding party?

75
00:04:03.872 --> 00:04:06.130
- What do you mean?
- Jerry's gonna be best man...

76
00:04:06.207 --> 00:04:08.466
and Kramer's the usher.
What am I gonna be?

77
00:04:08.626 --> 00:04:10.304
I don't think you're anything.

78
00:04:10.545 --> 00:04:14.974
Well. I have to be something.
I'm a close friend.

79
00:04:15.258 --> 00:04:18.312
- What about being a bridesmaid?
- Well. those are Susan's friends.

80
00:04:19.679 --> 00:04:24.157
- Then how about being an usher?
- All right. I'll ask Susan about it later.

81
00:04:24.226 --> 00:04:27.825
You don't ask. You tell.

82
00:04:30.941 --> 00:04:33.117
What about the letter?
Should I think about it?

83
00:04:33.193 --> 00:04:35.619
Elaine. if a guy wanted
to end a relationship...

84
00:04:35.696 --> 00:04:36.911
what could he do?

85
00:04:38.157 --> 00:04:40.000
Start smoking.

86
00:04:40.534 --> 00:04:42.461
Smoking.

87
00:04:42.536 --> 00:04:45.008
- Does she hate cigarettes?
- Yes. she hates cigarettes.

88
00:04:45.498 --> 00:04:47.341
But you don't smoke.

89
00:04:47.875 --> 00:04:49.932
No.

90
00:04:51.921 --> 00:04:54.856
You know. I think I'm getting
depressed about George's wedding.

91
00:04:54.924 --> 00:04:57.693
- Really?
- Yeah. once he gets married. that's it.

92
00:04:57.760 --> 00:05:00.434
She'll probably get pregnant.
They'll move to Westchester.

93
00:05:00.513 --> 00:05:03.531
- I'll never see him again.
- Yeah. you're probably right.

94
00:05:03.599 --> 00:05:06.487
- Then it'll be just me. you and Kramer.
- No. not me. pal.

95
00:05:06.561 --> 00:05:09.234
I can't keep this up much longer.
I'm sick of being single.

96
00:05:09.314 --> 00:05:11.987
- I'm getting out.
- So it's just gonna be me and Kramer?

97
00:05:12.067 --> 00:05:14.373
Yeah. just you and Kramer.

98
00:05:14.444 --> 00:05:16.003
See you.

99
00:05:16.863 --> 00:05:18.956
Me and Kramer.

100
00:05:20.033 --> 00:05:22.505
Hey. buddy.

101
00:05:22.828 --> 00:05:26.297
Hey. I thought of
a great invention for driving.

102
00:05:26.373 --> 00:05:29.557
A periscope in a car.
so you can see traffic.

103
00:05:29.626 --> 00:05:31.055
How are you gonna drive...

104
00:05:31.128 --> 00:05:33.635
while you're
looking through a periscope?

105
00:05:33.714 --> 00:05:35.522
Besides which. it's not a submarine.

106
00:05:35.591 --> 00:05:37.730
There's no room for a periscope
on a car.

107
00:05:37.801 --> 00:05:40.736
- Oh. you make a higher roof.
- They're not making higher roofs.

108
00:05:40.929 --> 00:05:42.737
Well. why can't you
make a higher roof?

109
00:05:43.390 --> 00:05:45.400
Because it's a stupid idea.

110
00:05:45.476 --> 00:05:48.861
No one's gonna go for it.
Don't you understand? It's stupid!

111
00:05:50.648 --> 00:05:52.372
Stupid. It's stupid.

112
00:05:53.818 --> 00:05:55.329
Hey. hey. hey. look out!

113
00:05:56.320 --> 00:05:58.543
Oh. my God. Are you okay?

114
00:05:58.614 --> 00:06:01.419
Yeah. thanks.

115
00:06:01.492 --> 00:06:03.549
Oh. my God. You saved my life.

116
00:06:03.619 --> 00:06:06.555
Shouldn't there be
some kind of reward for that?

117
00:06:07.540 --> 00:06:09.467
You should be careful
crossing the street.

118
00:06:09.542 --> 00:06:11.849
Otherwise you could die.
if that bothers you.

119
00:06:12.587 --> 00:06:15.937
- Well. yeah...
- See? To me. this is a waste.

120
00:06:16.257 --> 00:06:18.267
- What?
- The shirt under your sweater.

121
00:06:18.343 --> 00:06:20.270
It sits in a drawer for three weeks...

122
00:06:20.345 --> 00:06:23.731
and when it finally comes out.
it only sticks up out of your collar.

123
00:06:24.015 --> 00:06:26.191
- I'm Jerry Seinfeld.
- Jeannie Steinman.

124
00:06:26.518 --> 00:06:30.283
- Same initials. How do you like that?
- I like it.

125
00:06:31.356 --> 00:06:34.908
Listen. I was talking to Elaine today.
and she said...

126
00:06:34.985 --> 00:06:37.754
that she would really like
to be an usher at the wedding.

127
00:06:38.530 --> 00:06:40.539
No. out of the question.

128
00:06:40.616 --> 00:06:42.792
I don't want any women ushers
at my wedding.

129
00:06:42.868 --> 00:06:46.337
And while we're on the subject.
Kramer's not an usher either.

130
00:06:46.413 --> 00:06:49.087
- Why not?
- He doesn't even know my name.

131
00:06:49.500 --> 00:06:52.221
- That was an honest mistake.
- No. he's too weird.

132
00:06:52.294 --> 00:06:54.932
He'd fall or something.
He'd ruin the whole ceremony.

133
00:06:56.382 --> 00:06:58.640
Yeah. you're probably right.

134
00:07:02.096 --> 00:07:03.940
What are you doing?

135
00:07:06.517 --> 00:07:08.159
Since when do you smoke?

136
00:07:09.729 --> 00:07:11.822
I've always smoked.

137
00:07:12.440 --> 00:07:16.869
- I've never seen you smoke.
- Oh. yeah. well. big smoker.

138
00:07:17.070 --> 00:07:19.957
I gave it up for a while.
but it was too tough.

139
00:07:20.031 --> 00:07:23.796
You know. I don't got the willpower.

140
00:07:23.952 --> 00:07:28.714
- Oh. I don't like this one bit.
- Well. I can't stop now.

141
00:07:31.209 --> 00:07:34.144
I'm addicted.
They've gotten a hold on me.

142
00:07:34.588 --> 00:07:36.515
Well. you are gonna have to quit.

143
00:07:42.638 --> 00:07:44.362
- Menus?
- No. I know what I want.

144
00:07:44.431 --> 00:07:45.812
- The usual?
- Yeah.

145
00:07:45.891 --> 00:07:48.529
- And for you?
- A bowl of Cheerios. not too much milk.

146
00:07:48.602 --> 00:07:50.362
Okay. two bowls of Cheerios.

147
00:07:53.774 --> 00:07:55.285
- You too?
- Yeah.

148
00:07:57.653 --> 00:08:00.540
Hey. did you hear
the bank on the corner...

149
00:08:00.614 --> 00:08:04.547
is offering $100 if you go in there
and they don't greet you with a "hello."

150
00:08:04.952 --> 00:08:06.511
Oh. really? That's nice.

151
00:08:07.663 --> 00:08:10.337
- Come on. What's with you?
- I think I'm in love.

152
00:08:11.334 --> 00:08:13.391
Oh. come on.

153
00:08:13.586 --> 00:08:16.142
No. it's true.
This woman saved my life.

154
00:08:16.214 --> 00:08:18.639
I was crossing the street.
I was almost hit by a car.

155
00:08:18.716 --> 00:08:20.061
And then we talked...

156
00:08:20.134 --> 00:08:22.690
and the whole thing
just seemed like a dream.

157
00:08:22.762 --> 00:08:26.231
If a guy saved your life.
you'd be in love with him too.

158
00:08:27.058 --> 00:08:29.234
No. this woman is different.
She's incredible.

159
00:08:29.644 --> 00:08:32.781
She's just like me.
She talks like me. She acts like me.

160
00:08:32.856 --> 00:08:36.657
She ordered cereal in a restaurant.
We even have the same initials.

161
00:08:37.819 --> 00:08:40.327
- Wait. I just realized what's going on.
- What?

162
00:08:40.405 --> 00:08:43.293
Now I know what I've been
looking for all these years.

163
00:08:43.367 --> 00:08:45.127
Myself.

164
00:08:47.621 --> 00:08:51.007
I've been waiting
for me to come along.

165
00:08:51.083 --> 00:08:54.267
And now I've swept myself
off my feet.

166
00:08:56.088 --> 00:08:59.604
Will you stop it. man?
You're freaking me out.

167
00:08:59.675 --> 00:09:01.566
Jeez.

168
00:09:06.432 --> 00:09:07.777
- Hey.
- Hey.

169
00:09:08.017 --> 00:09:11.237
- Wait a second. you didn't say "hello."
- Yes. I did.

170
00:09:11.312 --> 00:09:13.784
No. No. you didn't.
Hundred dollars. I get $100.

171
00:09:13.856 --> 00:09:16.412
- No. no. I said "hello."
- No. no. you said "hey."

172
00:09:16.484 --> 00:09:18.826
Well. "hey" is "hello." Same thing.

173
00:09:18.903 --> 00:09:22.206
The ad said the bank will pay $100
if you're not greeted with a "hello."

174
00:09:22.282 --> 00:09:24.623
You're taking that much too literally.

175
00:09:24.701 --> 00:09:26.840
Now. sir. do you have
any business to transact?

176
00:09:26.911 --> 00:09:29.419
- I wanna speak with the manager.
- He's not here.

177
00:09:29.831 --> 00:09:31.639
Then I'll be back.

178
00:09:32.542 --> 00:09:34.635
- So I'm not gonna be an usher?
- No.

179
00:09:34.878 --> 00:09:36.472
So I'm nothing?

180
00:09:36.546 --> 00:09:40.774
Jerry is best man.
Kramer is an usher. and I am nothing?

181
00:09:41.009 --> 00:09:43.814
- Kramer's not an usher anymore.
- What are you talking about?

182
00:09:43.887 --> 00:09:45.814
- You've been demoted.
- Why?

183
00:09:45.889 --> 00:09:48.065
Because you called her
by the wrong name.

184
00:09:48.725 --> 00:09:51.233
But she really looks like a Lilly.

185
00:09:52.062 --> 00:09:55.994
Jerry. Hey. Jerry. Susan says
I can't be an usher at the wedding.

186
00:09:56.066 --> 00:09:57.660
Yeah. me neither.

187
00:09:57.735 --> 00:10:00.077
George. I wanna bring a date
to the wedding.

188
00:10:00.154 --> 00:10:02.412
- Who?
- I just met her. She's incredible.

189
00:10:02.490 --> 00:10:05.507
Oh. this is great!

190
00:10:05.576 --> 00:10:09.970
Now I'm gonna be stuck
at the singles' table with all the losers?

191
00:10:11.165 --> 00:10:13.887
- You can go with Kramer.
- No. no. no.

192
00:10:13.960 --> 00:10:16.598
Weddings are a great place
to meet chicks.

193
00:10:16.671 --> 00:10:19.178
I have to be unfettered.

194
00:10:20.091 --> 00:10:22.230
Do you see
what this is turning into?

195
00:10:22.302 --> 00:10:25.319
Do I need this?
I have got to get out of this thing.

196
00:10:25.388 --> 00:10:28.655
- Did you try the cigarettes?
- Yeah. they made me sick.

197
00:10:28.725 --> 00:10:32.028
All right. all right.
Let's get down here.

198
00:10:33.646 --> 00:10:35.538
You really wanna get out
of this thing?

199
00:10:36.483 --> 00:10:39.703
- Yeah.
- All right. I got two words for you;

200
00:10:39.778 --> 00:10:41.870
Prenup.

201
00:10:42.405 --> 00:10:43.881
Prenup. what does that mean?

202
00:10:43.949 --> 00:10:48.510
- Ask her to sign a prenup.
- What does that do?

203
00:10:48.578 --> 00:10:50.885
Because most women.
when asked to sign a prenup...

204
00:10:50.956 --> 00:10:53.677
are so offended.
they back out of the marriage.

205
00:10:54.668 --> 00:10:56.393
They are?

206
00:10:56.920 --> 00:10:59.856
- Elaine?
- I wouldn't sign one.

207
00:11:02.092 --> 00:11:05.561
Prenup. of course.

208
00:11:06.472 --> 00:11:09.407
- Kramer.
- Get out of here.

209
00:11:14.146 --> 00:11:15.622
- Hi.
- Hi.

210
00:11:15.690 --> 00:11:18.541
Hey. I've been going over the list.
Wanna invite The Drake?

211
00:11:18.609 --> 00:11:21.200
Oh. got to invite The Drake.

212
00:11:21.279 --> 00:11:22.873
Listen.

213
00:11:23.197 --> 00:11:25.207
There's something
that's been on my mind...

214
00:11:25.283 --> 00:11:29.333
and we haven't really talked about it
and it's kind of important to me.

215
00:11:29.746 --> 00:11:31.091
What is it?

216
00:11:31.164 --> 00:11:34.051
Well. I've put a lot of thought
into this...

217
00:11:34.125 --> 00:11:38.057
and I think that I would like you
to sign a prenuptial agreement.

218
00:11:39.047 --> 00:11:41.519
- A prenup?
- Yeah.

219
00:11:45.887 --> 00:11:47.861
What's so funny?

220
00:11:48.682 --> 00:11:52.115
You don't have any money.
I make more money than you do.

221
00:11:56.148 --> 00:11:59.332
Yeah. give me the papers.
I'll sign them.

222
00:12:01.320 --> 00:12:02.831
A prenup.

223
00:12:28.681 --> 00:12:30.655
Excuse me.

224
00:12:34.938 --> 00:12:36.746
Jerry.

225
00:12:37.899 --> 00:12:39.742
- Hey. Jeannie.
- Hello.

226
00:12:39.818 --> 00:12:41.957
- Remember I told you about the bank?
- Yeah.

227
00:12:42.028 --> 00:12:45.331
Well. I went in there
and they said. "hey."

228
00:12:46.032 --> 00:12:47.959
"Hey" is the same as "hello."
What do you think?

229
00:12:48.034 --> 00:12:50.044
Yeah. I think it's the same thing.

230
00:12:50.537 --> 00:12:53.306
Oh. big surprise.

231
00:12:59.880 --> 00:13:03.183
- Delivery from Melody Stationers.
- Oh. those are the invitations.

232
00:13:03.258 --> 00:13:05.316
- Just sign here.
- Yeah.

233
00:13:06.345 --> 00:13:07.939
Thank you.

234
00:13:08.180 --> 00:13:10.237
- See you later.
- Oh. these are so cheap.

235
00:13:10.307 --> 00:13:12.614
Don't forget tomorrow.
We're shopping for rings...

236
00:13:12.685 --> 00:13:16.652
so don't make any plans.
And this time we're not skimping.

237
00:13:17.940 --> 00:13:19.582
- Hey.
- Hey.

238
00:13:19.650 --> 00:13:21.707
- Jeannie left?
- Yeah. she's coming to see...

239
00:13:21.777 --> 00:13:24.499
- my act tonight.
- Oh. yeah? Well. that's nice.

240
00:13:24.572 --> 00:13:27.377
I'm sure that's right up her alley.

241
00:13:27.450 --> 00:13:29.009
- What's with you?
- Nothing.

242
00:13:29.076 --> 00:13:30.375
- Something on your mind?
- No.

243
00:13:30.453 --> 00:13:31.833
- Looks like there is.
- No.

244
00:13:31.913 --> 00:13:34.634
Come on. something's
on your mind. Out with it.

245
00:13:34.749 --> 00:13:37.007
I don't like her!

246
00:13:37.210 --> 00:13:38.970
- You don't like her?
- That's right.

247
00:13:39.045 --> 00:13:42.312
I don't like her.
I never liked her from the get-go.

248
00:13:42.715 --> 00:13:45.389
- What's wrong with her?
- Everything she thinks. you think.

249
00:13:45.468 --> 00:13:47.976
Everything you think. she thinks.
No. I can't take it.

250
00:13:48.054 --> 00:13:51.523
I can't take it. Jerry.
It's too much. It's too much.

251
00:13:51.600 --> 00:13:53.906
If you can't take her.
maybe you can't take me.

252
00:13:54.102 --> 00:13:57.203
- So that's how it's gonna be?
- That's how it's gonna be.

253
00:13:57.272 --> 00:14:00.373
Oh. God help us!

254
00:14:08.617 --> 00:14:10.259
Awful.

255
00:14:54.915 --> 00:14:57.470
- Can I help you?
- Yeah.

256
00:14:58.752 --> 00:15:01.639
I was in here the other day.
and I went up to that teller...

257
00:15:01.713 --> 00:15:03.307
and he didn't say "hello."

258
00:15:04.007 --> 00:15:07.061
Well. then you are entitled to $100.
That's our policy.

259
00:15:07.135 --> 00:15:09.312
Yeah. but he wouldn't
give me the money.

260
00:15:09.555 --> 00:15:11.481
Jim. can I see you for a second?

261
00:15:11.974 --> 00:15:16.154
- Yes. can you give me a minute?
- Yeah.

262
00:15:16.228 --> 00:15:19.495
He'll be right over.

263
00:15:30.785 --> 00:15:32.165
What is this. oak?

264
00:15:34.205 --> 00:15:37.591
- I think it's pine.
- Pine is good.

265
00:15:37.834 --> 00:15:40.010
Yeah. pine's okay.

266
00:15:44.007 --> 00:15:45.352
- You wanted to see me?
- Yeah.

267
00:15:45.425 --> 00:15:48.479
Jim. the man here
says he came in the other day...

268
00:15:48.553 --> 00:15:51.061
- you didn't say "hello."
- No. that's not true.

269
00:15:51.139 --> 00:15:54.275
I said "hey." You know.
like a friendly greeting. "hey."

270
00:15:54.351 --> 00:15:57.202
- Yeah. but that's not "hello."
- That's a tough one.

271
00:15:58.813 --> 00:16:00.823
Let me bring
some other people in on this.

272
00:16:00.899 --> 00:16:05.376
Barbara. Jane. Mike.
can I see you. please?

273
00:16:08.073 --> 00:16:09.715
- How you doing?
- What's happening?

274
00:16:09.783 --> 00:16:11.425
What's up?

275
00:16:12.536 --> 00:16:16.087
Can you excuse us
for just one minute? Just one minute.

276
00:16:16.874 --> 00:16:18.516
Thanks.

277
00:16:22.963 --> 00:16:24.807
How's it going?

278
00:16:26.008 --> 00:16:28.065
Thanks. Thanks. everybody.

279
00:16:29.970 --> 00:16:32.941
Sir. have a seat.

280
00:16:36.185 --> 00:16:40.235
Well. we've discussed this.
Here's the feeling.

281
00:16:40.398 --> 00:16:43.250
You got a greeting. It starts with an H.
How's 20 bucks sound?

282
00:16:43.317 --> 00:16:44.995
- I'll take it.
- All right. sir.

283
00:17:02.379 --> 00:17:04.602
Will you marry me?

284
00:17:19.438 --> 00:17:22.741
I would like to propose a toast...
Wait a second!

285
00:17:22.816 --> 00:17:25.454
George! George Costanza.
come in here!

286
00:17:25.527 --> 00:17:27.335
- Georgie boy.
- George. big news.

287
00:17:27.404 --> 00:17:29.544
- I'm getting married.
- Married? What?

288
00:17:29.615 --> 00:17:33.582
September 21st. first day of autumn.
Leaves changing. beautiful colours.

289
00:17:33.661 --> 00:17:35.041
- All that crap.
- You see?

290
00:17:35.121 --> 00:17:37.628
- I kept up my end of the pact.
- Oh. good for you.

291
00:17:37.707 --> 00:17:39.716
- And look. champagne.
- Hey.

292
00:17:39.792 --> 00:17:42.466
- To our future wives.
- Oh. yeah.

293
00:17:42.545 --> 00:17:44.269
Yeah.

294
00:17:57.143 --> 00:18:00.078
This has been quite a night.
I could sure use a cup of coffee.

295
00:18:00.146 --> 00:18:02.868
Hey. what's the deal with decaf?

296
00:18:02.941 --> 00:18:04.868
How do they get the caffeine
out of there?

297
00:18:04.943 --> 00:18:07.997
- And then where does it go?
- I don't know.

298
00:18:11.366 --> 00:18:13.091
That's a shame.

299
00:18:14.494 --> 00:18:17.002
- I'll just have a cup of coffee.
- Bowl of corn flakes.

300
00:18:18.373 --> 00:18:20.431
More cereal?
That's your third bowl today.

301
00:18:20.500 --> 00:18:24.219
- You had it for breakfast and lunch.
- Hey. So. what's the deal with brunch?

302
00:18:24.296 --> 00:18:26.472
If it's a combination
of breakfast and lunch...

303
00:18:26.548 --> 00:18:29.602
how come there's no "lupper."
or no "linner"?

304
00:18:34.682 --> 00:18:36.324
Hey!

305
00:18:36.600 --> 00:18:39.370
Frank just called me.
Congratulations.

306
00:18:39.437 --> 00:18:42.870
- Thanks. Thanks.
- Look. I'm sorry about before.

307
00:18:42.940 --> 00:18:46.290
- I'm sure I'll learn to like her. Jerry.
- Yeah. yeah.

308
00:18:46.360 --> 00:18:49.248
Come on. come on.
What's the matter?

309
00:18:50.448 --> 00:18:52.706
I think I may have
made a big mistake.

310
00:18:54.118 --> 00:18:56.792
- Oh. come on.
- No. all of a sudden it hit me.

311
00:18:56.871 --> 00:18:58.513
I realized what the problem is.

312
00:18:58.581 --> 00:19:00.721
I can't be with someone like me.

313
00:19:00.792 --> 00:19:02.968
I hate myself!

314
00:19:03.253 --> 00:19:05.760
I need to be with someone
the complete opposite of me.

315
00:19:05.839 --> 00:19:08.975
It's too much. Kramer.
I can't take it! I can't take it!

316
00:19:10.385 --> 00:19:13.356
It's too bad you got engaged.

317
00:19:13.847 --> 00:19:15.904
Yeah. too bad.

318
00:19:17.350 --> 00:19:19.408
Hello? Oh. hey. George.

319
00:19:19.478 --> 00:19:22.614
What? Really?

320
00:19:22.689 --> 00:19:25.078
I'll call Elaine.
We'll meet you down there.

321
00:19:25.150 --> 00:19:27.575
- What happened?
- They took Susan to the hospital.

322
00:19:29.029 --> 00:19:31.585
- So she was just lying there?
- Yeah.

323
00:19:31.657 --> 00:19:33.584
- I wonder what happened.
- I don't know.

324
00:19:33.659 --> 00:19:35.917
There's the doctor.

325
00:19:36.954 --> 00:19:38.762
Excuse me. are you the husband?

326
00:19:39.373 --> 00:19:45.891
- Well. not yet. Fiancé.
- Yes. Well. I'm sorry.

327
00:19:45.963 --> 00:19:47.771
She's gone.

328
00:19:50.468 --> 00:19:52.110
What's that?

329
00:19:53.846 --> 00:19:55.275
She expired.

330
00:19:58.601 --> 00:20:00.528
Are you sure?

331
00:20:02.146 --> 00:20:03.622
Yes. of course.

332
00:20:04.107 --> 00:20:06.496
So...

333
00:20:06.568 --> 00:20:07.948
she's dead?

334
00:20:10.363 --> 00:20:11.792
Yes.

335
00:20:16.703 --> 00:20:18.178
Let me ask you...

336
00:20:18.246 --> 00:20:24.017
had she been exposed
to any kind of inexpensive glue?

337
00:20:26.672 --> 00:20:28.811
- Why?
- We found traces...

338
00:20:28.882 --> 00:20:31.734
of a certain toxic adhesive...

339
00:20:31.802 --> 00:20:35.900
commonly found
in very low-priced envelopes.

340
00:20:36.974 --> 00:20:39.779
Well. she was sending out
our wedding invitations.

341
00:20:40.644 --> 00:20:43.282
That's probably what did it.

342
00:20:44.064 --> 00:20:47.000
We were expecting
about 200 people.

343
00:20:49.403 --> 00:20:53.916
Well. thank you. doctor.

344
00:21:11.176 --> 00:21:13.233
She's...

345
00:21:14.095 --> 00:21:15.690
gone.

346
00:21:17.098 --> 00:21:18.776
Dead?

347
00:21:20.018 --> 00:21:25.076
I'm so sorry. George.

348
00:21:25.941 --> 00:21:27.998
Yeah. me too.

349
00:21:30.779 --> 00:21:32.077
Poor Lilly.

350
00:21:32.155 --> 00:21:34.165
- Susan.
- Susan.

351
00:21:39.455 --> 00:21:42.128
- How did it happen?
- Apparently the glue...

352
00:21:42.207 --> 00:21:45.558
in the wedding invitations was...

353
00:21:46.712 --> 00:21:48.520
toxic.

354
00:21:51.634 --> 00:21:53.477
Well. that's weird.

355
00:21:55.054 --> 00:21:57.111
So I guess...

356
00:21:57.682 --> 00:22:00.985
- you're not getting married.
- Yeah.

357
00:22:02.770 --> 00:22:04.364
But....

358
00:22:05.982 --> 00:22:10.032
- Yeah?
- Well. now I'm engaged.

359
00:22:10.361 --> 00:22:11.706
Yeah?

360
00:22:11.988 --> 00:22:14.081
Well. I thought
we'd both be getting married.

361
00:22:15.075 --> 00:22:17.748
Hey. what can I tell you?

362
00:22:17.952 --> 00:22:19.251
All right.

363
00:22:20.830 --> 00:22:22.923
Well. let's get some coffee.

364
00:22:24.084 --> 00:22:26.591
We had a pact!

365
00:22:34.136 --> 00:22:37.687
Yes. I'd like to speak
with Marisa Tomei. please.

366
00:22:39.308 --> 00:22:43.571
Marisa. hi. It's George Costanza.

367
00:22:43.687 --> 00:22:48.366
I'm the short. funny. quirky
bald man you met a little while ago.

368
00:22:48.442 --> 00:22:50.998
Yeah. I was just calling
because I wanted you to know...

369
00:22:51.070 --> 00:22:54.455
that I'm not engaged anymore.

370
00:22:54.907 --> 00:22:57.379
Well. she died.

371
00:22:58.077 --> 00:23:01.427
Toxic glue
from the wedding invitations.

372
00:23:02.039 --> 00:23:04.975
Well. we were expecting
about 200 people.

373
00:23:05.251 --> 00:23:06.428
Yeah.

374
00:23:06.469 --> 00:23:10.333
Anyway. I've got the
funeral tomorrow but...

375
00:23:11.799 --> 00:23:14.473
my weekend is
pretty wide open...

376
00:23:15.220 --> 00:23:18.653
and. you know.
I was wondering... Hello?

377
00:23:18.723 --> 00:23:20.483
Hello?
